Load packages

library(tidyverse); library(lme4); library(mgcv); library(sitar); library(lspline); library(splines); library(broom.mixed); library(ggeffects); library(metafor)

Load BMI dataset

dat <- read.csv((
  "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aelhak/NCRM2023/main/bmi_long.csv")) %>% 
  mutate(id = as.factor(id), sex = as.factor(sex))

dat_m <- dat %>% filter(sex == "M")
dat_f <- dat %>% filter(sex == "F")

Quick look at the data

with(dat, plot(age, bmi))

dat %>% group_by(sex) %>% summarise(N = n_distinct(id))
## # A tibble: 2  2
##   sex       N
##   <fct> <int>
## 1 F       100
## 2 M       100
dat %>% group_by(id) %>% count() %>% ungroup() %>% 
  summarise(median(n), min(n), max(n))
## # A tibble: 1  3
##   `median(n)` `min(n)` `max(n)`
##         <dbl>    <int>    <int>
## 1          11        1       21

Linear splines

Males

Fit models with different knots and select model with lowest BIC

ls_m <- map(3:6, possibly(~ { eval(parse(text = paste0(
  "lmer(bmi ~ qlspline(age, ", .x, ") + (qlspline(age, 2) | id ), 
  REML = F, data = dat_m)")))}, otherwise = NA_real_))

(ls_m_best <- ls_m[[which.min(unlist(map(ls_m, BIC)))]])
## Linear mixed model fit by maximum likelihood  ['lmerMod']
## Formula: bmi ~ qlspline(age, 6) + (qlspline(age, 2) | id)

Restricted cubic splines

Males

Fit models with different knots and select model with lowest BIC

rcs_m <- map(3:6, possibly(~ { eval(parse(text = paste0(
  "lmer(bmi ~ ns(age, ", .x, ") + (ns(age, 2) | id ), 
  REML = F, data = dat_m)")))}, otherwise = NA_real_))

(rcs_m_best <- rcs_m[[which.min(unlist(map(rcs_m, BIC)))]])

P-splines

Males

m_gamm <- gamm(
  bmi ~ s(log(age), bs = 'ps', k = 10, m = c(2, 2)) + 
  s(log(age), id, bs = "fs", xt = "ps", k = 10, m = c(2, 1)),
  method = "REML", data = dat_m)
## Warning in gam.side(sm, X, tol = .Machine$double.eps^0.5): model has repeated 1-
## d smooths of same variable.

SITAR

Load height dataset

ht_dat <- berkeley %>% 
  filter(age >= 5 & age <= 20) %>% 
  select(id, sex, age, height) %>% 
  drop_na()

ht_dat_m <- ht_dat %>% filter(sex == 1)
ht_dat_f <- ht_dat %>% filter(sex == 2)
